      <notesStmt>
        <note>A tied book containing four texts: Bhagavatīpadmapuṣpāñjali by Rāmakṛṣṇa (pp. 1-12), Śivastotra (pp. 14-15), Somavāravratapūjāvidhi (pp. 19-25), and Achidravrata (pp. 27-28).</note>
        <note>Title Bhagavatīpadmapuṣpāñjali from colophon p. 12. Title Śivastotra supplied by ms. label and used by Poleman. Title Somavāravratapūjāvidhi from colophon p. 25. Title Achidravrata supplied by cataloger.</note>
        <note>Written 8-10 lines per leaf on country paper.</note>
        <note>Fair condition. Orange powder rubbed in over invocations, colophons, numbers, and section headings. Mistakes written over or indicated by short diagonal or vertical strokes.</note>
        <note>Cover has drawing in black of a 10-armed goddess, presumably Durgā, with her mount. Picture partially obscured by reddish-brown splotches.</note>
        <note>Bhagavatīpadmapuṣpāñjali begins (p. 1): śrīgaṇeśāya namaḥ om̐ namaḥ caṇḍikāyai namaḥ śambho namaḥ om̐ bhagavatībhagavatpadapaṅkajaṁ bhramarabhūtasurāsurasevitaṁ* sujanamānasahaṁsapariskṛtaṁ kamalayāmalayānibhṛtaṁ bhaje (verse 1).</note>
        <note>Colophon to Bhagavatīpadmapuṣpāñjali (p. 12): iti śrīrāma[kṛ]ṣṇaviracitaṁ bhagavatīpadmapuṣpāñjaliḥ sampūrṇaṁ.</note>
        <note>Śivastotra begins (p. 14): śrīgaṇeśāya namaḥ om̐ namaḥ jayadeva jayādeva jayājeya jayaśaṅkaraśāśvata jayasarvasurādhyakṣa jayasarvasurārcitta (verse 1).</note>
        <note>Colophon to Śivastotra (p. 16): iti mama vadatodināniyātu* smara hara kiṁ vahajalpakalpanābhiḥ [?] ( verse 15).</note>
        <note>A new, unnamed text begins on f. 16, which is left off after two lines (pp. 17-18 blank).</note>
        <note>Somavāravratapūjāvidhi begins (pp. 19-25): śrīgaṇeśāya namaḥ atha somavāravratapūjāvidhiḥ. tatra kartā [o?]cirācat̄taḥ bhuktāmbaradharaḥ kṛtyakriyaḥ pradoṣasamaye [u?]da[ṅktu?]khopaveśyācamya</note>
        <note>Colophon to Somavāravratapūjāvidhi (p. 25): iti somavāravratapūjāvidhiḥ samāptāḥ śubhm.</note>
        <note>Achidravrata begins (p. 27): śrīgaṇeśāya namaḥ atha a[ch]idraḥ vratānāṁ vratarājendravratānāṁ vratam uttamaṁ vratachidraṁ tapachidraṁ yachidraṁ yajñakarmaṇi (verse 1).</note>
        <note>Achidravrata ends (p. 28): śrīviṣọprasādāt vrāhmaṇavacanāt sarvaṁ paripūrṇam astu paripūrṇatāstu. śubhm.</note>
      </notesStmt>
